== 旅行限制 ==
因为疫情，许多国家和地区对受灾严重地区的公民以及近期去过的旅行者实行了隔离，入境禁令或其他限制。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions.html|title=Coronavirus Travel Restrictions, Across the Globe|date=2020-03-26|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2020-08-29|archive-date=2020-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200612021308/https://www.nytimes.com/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>其他国家和地区也已施加了适用于所有外国和地区的全球旅行限令，或阻止本国公民出国旅行。<ref>{{cite web|title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) – information for Australian travellers|url=https://www.smartraveller.gov.au/COVID-19-australian-travellers|date=2020-04-09|publisher=Australian Government|accessdate=2020-08-29|archive-date=2020-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414132542/https://www.smartraveller.gov.au/COVID-19-australian-travellers|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

加上旅行意愿的下降，这些限制对地区的旅游业产生了不利的经济影响。大量商务旅行和国际会议改为非实地举行的线上会议可能对本地经济造成长期的影响。<ref>{{cite web|title=The long-term effects of the coronavirus|url=https://www.jpost.com/Opinion/The-long-term-effects-of-the-coronavirus-619118|website=The Jerusalem Post {{!}} JPost.com|access-date=2020-03-12|archive-date=2020-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308084506/https://www.jpost.com/Opinion/The-long-term-effects-of-the-coronavirus-619118|dead-url=no}}</ref>因此，许多人对于因疫情而推出的旅行限令的有效性提出了不少质疑。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nsikan|first1=Akpan|title=Coronavirus spikes outside China show travel bans aren't working|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/02/why-travel-restrictions-are-not-stopping-coronavirus-covid-19/|accessdate=2020-04-02|work=National Geographic|date=2020-02-24|language=en|archive-date=2020-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411141838/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/02/why-travel-restrictions-are-not-stopping-coronavirus-covid-19/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

